# ================================================================
# Make.local.example — template for machine-local build settings
#
# Copy this file to Make.local and edit as needed.
# Make.local is already listed in .gitignore so your local paths
# will not be committed to the repository.
#
# HOW HDF5 PATH INJECTION WORKS:
#   Set HDF5_HOME to the HDF5 install prefix.  AMReX's Make.hdf5
#   picks up HDF5_HOME and appends include/ and lib/ automatically.
#   Do NOT manually add -I / -L / -lhdf5 here — that causes
#   duplicate flags and link-order issues.
#
# PARALLEL HDF5:
#   Parallel HDF5 is determined by the HDF5 library itself (whether
#   it was built with MPI).  Simply point HDF5_HOME at a
#   parallel-enabled install and set USE_MPI=TRUE.
# ================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Example: custom HDF5 install (source-built or Spack)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# USE_HDF5 = TRUE
# HDF5_HOME = $(HOME)/hdf5-parallel

# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Example: HPC system with environment modules
# Cray/Spack module sets HDF5_DIR automatically; no path needed.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# USE_HDF5 = TRUE
# AMREX_HDF5_HOME = $(HDF5_DIR)
